description: Recently sold: $450,000. A private oasis surrounded by 5-acres of whispering pines, rolling landscape and a pond view. This classic 2-story home with charming front porch offers 5 beds and 4 baths. Enter the inviting 2-story foyer with gorgeous inlaid wood floors. The main level is sure to delight with an updated kitchen w/ granite counters, stainless appliances, convection/microwave and center island. Cozy up to a beautiful gas fireplace and entertain in the formal family and dining rooms. Atrium doors step onto an oversized, multi-level deck. The large master suite provides a private bath and walk-in closet. This great floor plan includes 3 beds on upper level. The finished walkout lower level has a rec room, 2 beds, a 3/4 bath and a flex room.  Bring your horses and livestock to roam the fully fenced in pasture and a massive 70 x 30 ft barn. The outbuilding provides heated floors, 12 ft doors on both ends and 220 VAC. Lot is conveniently irrigated offering a plush green lawn. New steel siding & carpet.

description:
Recently sold: $449,900. Prepare to be blown away!
Drive under the Ranch entrance to this beauty that is resting on nearly 5 acres and is surrounded by mature trees and lavish landscaping.
A circle driveway gives a glimpse of the maintenance-free exterior with a farm-style front porch, brick, stone, and vinyl allowing for much time to spend on the two-tiered 20x14 deck that is just off the incredible kitchen. A walk-in pantry and new stainless steel appliances add beauty to this space and make mealtime a breeze.
Hardwood flooring covers the dining room for an impressive and clean look.
Enter the private Master sanctuary through French doors and grab your favorite novel to enjoy near the box window and watch the wildlife outside. A walk-in closet stores all belongings neat and tidy. The luxurious Master bath has dual sinks and a separate bath and shower.
Arched doorways with pillar accents adorn the family rec room complete with a gorgeous gas fireplace flanked by custom built-ins to display prized possessions. A tray vault adds dimension and Knotty Pine cabinetry holds a wine fridge for entertaining.
Keep all the maintenance items stored away in the 58x36 outbuilding. Incredible!
Presented by the Chris Fritch Team Keller Williams Classic Realty 763-746-3997

description: Recently sold: $900,000. With southern exposure overlooking the Mississippi River, this custom designed one owner home features gracious public rooms and easily accommodates a work from home scenario. Library, living room and banquet sized dining room all feature fireplaces. Vaulted music room with large office behind rotating bookshelf, generous kitchen with dual islands and pantries, and solarium/family room. Five bedrooms on 2nd level plus 3rd floor bonus room. Riprapped shoreline with dock, expansive yard with fire pit and terrace. Located on a "recreational pool" where the River allows larger boats at higher speeds. This is a unique retreat just 25 min. from Minneapolis and just 1.8 miles to the Northstar commuter rail station in Anoka!

description:
Recently sold: $325,000. 4 Bedroom, 4 Bath Single Family Home (2786sq. ft. 4-level) on 1.31 acres in Ramsey, MN for Sale
-Constructed in 1978
-Attached 2 car garage w/ openers, keyless entry, access doors to kitchen, entryway, & backyard
-Vaulted ceilings, 6 panel doors
-Central Air & Forced air heat
-Used appliances included, not warrantied: Refrigerator, electric convection oven, microwave, dishwasher, clothes washer, dryer, water heater, central air/furnace, water softener
-Wood deck, 2 patio areas 
-Newer shingles & siding 
-Unbelievable amounts of storage 
-Private well
-Mound septic system

Main Floor
-Ex. Lg. entry area, direct access to attached garage.  Large closet w/ paneled doors, long hanging bar w/ upper & lower shelving for shoe and boot storage, built-in sitting bench. 2 windows, electrical outlets, recessed night-light, glass paneled door to buffer cold/heat while entering the main living area from the front or garage doors
-Bath #1: 1/2 bath available upon exiting the entryway, close proximity to dining room & kitchen. Solid wood door, water efficient tall-seat toilet, small hand sink
-Utility closet w/ shelving, internal light switch, electrical outlet
-Large dining area can accommodate a long dining table, seating for12+ adults, large chandelier
-Study area located off dining room, laminate flooring, 4 windows, lighted ceiling fan, door to access the back yard. 3 windows
-Kitchen w/ direct access to garage
-Electric convection oven, microwave with night light, dishwasher, refrigerator/ice maker. 16 over & lower wood cabinets, small pantry/utility closet, 10 drawers, 2 cutting boards. Extra large over sink window
Upper Floor
-Carpeted half staircase, leads to upper level
-Extra large formal living area w/ patio door access to the deck, vaulted ceilings, lighted ceiling fan w/ remote control, partial privacy wall to divide the living room and dining room
-Extra wide carpeted hallway leads to the main bathroom, 2 bedrooms, master suite, and deep-set linen closet
-Bath # 2: Main full bath- tub, shower, single sink, beveled mirror, and water efficient toilet.  Additional storage located behind the door
-Bedroom # 1:  One window, lighted ceiling fan, full size closet w/ long hanging bar & upper shelf
-Bedroom #2: One window, lighted ceiling fan, deep closet w/ one long hanging bar and upper shelf, and 2 shorter hanging bars with storage shelves
-Master Bedroom #3, Bath #3:  2 windows, carpeted, lighted ceiling fan w/ remote, full sized closet w/ long hanging bar, upper shelving, laundry chute. Has  3/4 bath w/ single sink, beveled mirror, toilet, shower w/ glass door, extra large recessed storage cabinet
Lower Level
-Finished ex. large open rec-room, divided by a partial wall and different floor coverings, gives the illusion of two separate areas. 3 windows, exterior door leading to a patio, available wood burning stove
-Laundry Room/Bath #4: HE washer, electric dryer, furnace, water heater, & air exchanger, utility sink, tall-seat toilet, storage cabinet
-Bedroom #4: Carpeted, suspended ceiling, and open closet. 2 windows 
Basement

More than 450sq. ft. of storage space!
Garage
-23ft. x 25ft/575sq. ft. 
-Small exterior door w/ screened door for backyard access
-2 interior doors allow entry to entryway and kitchen
-Attic storage in rafters with fold-down ladder. Attic area has lighting and light switch
Storage Shed
-Extra tall utility shed large enough to park a riding lawn mower, wheel barrows, snow blowers, and a whole lot more
-Extra heavy duty construction
-Interior lighting
-Roll up door
Pole Shed:
-24ft. x24ft.
-Attached Lean-To 
-Tall enough to store small skid loader/tractor/loader.
-Separate driveway access and very large parking area at the rear of the building
-Tall manual opening door, locks from inside.
-One man door, two windows
-Heated
-Wired with 110/220 voltage for welders or other high voltage equipment

description:

description:
Recently sold: $395,000. Contact the official listing agent, Kristy Olson with Realty Group Inc, for the most accurate and up to date information on this property.

There is nothing "cookie cutter" about this one-of-a-kind charmer, located on 1.17 acres which backs to the Rum River Hills Golf Course. Are you ready to host some Backyard BBQs and Pool Parties? The salt water chlorine generator keeps the pool maintenance to a minimum. And when those MN mosquitoes are getting you down, enjoy evenings sitting in the beautiful 3-season porch. It doesn't get much better than this. 5 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms with in-floor heat, Master bath with a deep soak tub, "His & Hers" offices, a truly GREAT great room on the main level, which walks out to the spectacular backyard, and so much more. Be sure to ask your agent for this home's Features List!

Recently sold: $166,000. Welcome home to carefree and affordable living in Ramsey! Neat & clean end unit built in 2005. BBQ to your heart's content on patio off kitchen in back. description:
Recently sold: $188,000. This end-unit townhome is a step above the rest with many upgrades. Enjoy brand new stainless steel Frigidaire Gallery kitchen appliances and new carpet on the second floor. The first floor has laminate hardwood flooring throughout with ceramic tile in the guest bathroom. The interior has neutral paint colors throughout and the second floor shines with recessed lighting and vaulted ceilings. Need a third bedroom? The builder included an option to convert the den to a bedroom. Original floorplan options are available for review. The home comes equipped with an ADT alarm system and the garage is more than just a garage with heavy-duty shelving, improved lighting, and a workbench. This is a well-maintained one-owner home. 

Nestled in quiet Cove of Mississippi West, this home is uniquely situated near the Mississippi river, walking trails, a park, grocery store, highway access, and the Northstar Commuter Rail. The townhome association offers one of the lowest association dues in the area at $168/month, which includes water and septic! It?s maintenance free living without breaking the bank! Move-in ready. Available for showing May 5, 2019. Quick closing. This home will not last long.

Please schedule a showing today. Buyers agents will receive a 3% seller-paid commission.

Recently sold: $419,000. Welcome to the Northfork at Ramsey! Gorgeous home situated on over 2 acres backing up to LakeItasca with spectacular views of environmental lake. Fantastic open main floor plan features familyroom stone wood burning fireplace centered between LR and large kitchen with eat-in and centerisland. Main floor includes maple cabinets and floors with walkout to three season porch or largedeck for entertaining or relaxing with a book and listening to the calls of nature. Upper 3 bedroomsinclude large master suite with sitting room. The walkout basement is ready to be finished withyour touches and features 2nd fireplace. A gorgeous home on a desired lot - this is the one youhave been waiting to hit the market!

description: Recently sold: $308,900. Welcome to this beautiful Ramsey Home nestled on a 2 acre wooded lot on a quiet cul-de-sac just a couple of blocks to the hiking and biking trails of Elmcrest Park.  The kitchen is awesome with new maple cabinets, ceramic backsplash, and stainless appliances.  A large peninsula provides a lot of extra counter space.  The dining area is off the kitchen and living room.  A sliding door leads to a large deck overlooking the back yard.  The living room has a wood burning fireplace and wood floors.  There are 2 bedrooms up and a 3rd on the lower level.  The upper bath was remodeled and shows well.  The lower level also has a large family room 2nd bath, and walkout laundry.  A separate 4 season porch is nicely finished and could be used as a shop or guest quarters.  There is also a gazebo in the back yard and provides hours of bug free relaxing.  The septic was recently replaced and is up to code.  You will love the private lot and many trees. The City of Ramsey is approximately 29 square miles in area, has a population of approximately 23,670, and is fortunate to be known for its natural resources. It is located 21 miles from Minneapolis.  More than half of the City borders the Rum and Mississippi Rivers, and over 15 percent of its area is protected wetlands.  The Links at Northfork Golf Course is a 4-star Golf Digest-rated Championship golf course located in Ramsey. The course is open to the public and has a reputation for superior playing conditions and unmatched practice facilities. The Links provides challenging and memorable experience for golfers of all skill levels.  Rum River Hills Golf Club is also located in Ramsey. irections: 47 N TO 160TH LN NW, W 1 BLOCK TO NEON STREET
